The power rating of a transistor typically decreases as temperature increases, and this decrease can be quantified as a percentage of the transistor's maximum rated power at a specific temperature. However, the exact percentage decrease will depend on the specific transistor, its design, and other factors. Thus, the answer to your question will depend on the specific transistor model and other details not provided in your question.

In general, power transistors can operate at elevated temperatures for short periods of time without significant damage, but operating temperatures should be kept within the recommended range specified by the manufacturer to ensure optimal performance and reliability.
